Title: Algebraic Linearization of Dynamics of Calogero Type for any Coxeter
  Group
Authors: R. Caseiro (Coimbra), J.-P. Francoise (Paris VI) and R. Sasaki (Kyoto)
Comments: LaTeX2e, 13 pages, no figures
Report-no: YITP-99-73
Subj-class: High Energy Physics - Theory; Mathematical Physics; Exactly
  Solvable and Integrable Systems
Journal-ref: J.Math.Phys. 41 (2000) 4679-4686
\\
  Calogero-Moser systems can be generalized for any root system (including the
non-crystallographic cases). The algebraic linearization of the generalized
Calogero-Moser systems and of their quadratic (resp. quartic) perturbations are
discussed.
